main event: A civilian woman in Englewood, Colorado reported seeing a single unidentified flying object on December 21, 1966 around 2:15-2:30 AM.
interesting points: The object appeared to be the popular image of a 'flying saucer' with a very bright light in the center that was blinking.
The object was observed for about 2 minutes, during which it moved in a straight line, stopped, backed up, then went down behind the mountains.
The object was observed with the naked eye and appeared to be very high above the mountains.
The weather was clear with no winds, and there were no other notable meteorological or astronomical conditions reported.
No photographs were taken of the object.
sighted object: single unidentified flying object with a 'flying saucer' appearance and a blinking bright light
